{"lemma":"جار","slug":"جار","root":"ج.ر.#","root_slug":"ج-ر-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ج-ر-_","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"جار","root":"جور","pos":"N","occurrence_count":3},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":11},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n4881","n4882","n5407","n5641","n6665","n6672"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AC%D8%A7%D8%B1"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to deviate, to stray"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to commit an outrage, to wrong, to persecute, to oppress, to tyrannize"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to encroach, to make inroads"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be in the neighborhood of, to live nextdoor to"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to adjoin"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be in the vicinity, to be close to"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to border"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"neighbor","examples":[{"text":"جَارُنَا الْجَدِيدُ شَخْصٌ لَطِيفٌ وَوَدُودٌ.","english":"Our new neighbor is a kind and friendly person."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"refugee"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"protégé, charge"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"active participle of جَرَى (jarā)","tags":["active","form-of","participle"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-West Semitic *gawar-.\n\nIf we assume a pronunciation /ɔː/ for ā in ancient Ḥijāzi dialects of Arabic, as is also found necessary to be posited for other borrowings as قَيُّوم (qayyūm) and to make the Ethiopian Semitic borrowings of the present word phonologically plausible, then it is possible to conceive this word loaned from copiously attested Aramaic גיורא / ܓܝܘܪܐ (gīyōrā, “alien; proselyte”), functionally equivalent to Ugaritic 𐎂𐎗 (gr, “foreign resident, protected guest”) and Hebrew גֵּר (gēr, “alien; proselyte”) of which the feminine is גִיוֹרֶת (giyyṓreṯ, “proselyte”), while the specific meaning of a “neighbour” is found developed in Palestinian Aramaic מגירה / ܡܓܝܪܐ (məḡīrā), Northwest Semitic derivations of Proto-West Semitic *gawar- in the sense of ”to encroach upon the limits of, to assail, to come over” (while inheritance from Proto-West Semitic of the present noun per se would be difficult to construct); for the simplification of the shape of the word regard Arabic حُوت (ḥūt, “fish; whale”).\n\nDerived from the active participle of جَرَى (jarā)."},"ipa":["/d͡ʒaːr/","/d͡ʒaː.rin/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n4881","headword_ar":"جَاَرَ","root":"jA^r","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"juw^aArN","text_ar":"جُوَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA^or","text_ar":"جَاْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a bull, S and K, or a calf, A,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA^orato","text_ar":"جَاْرَتْ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"she,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a cow, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lowed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"juw^aArN","text_ar":"جُوَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuwaArN","text_ar":"خُوَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and is substituted for the latter in a reading of the Kur vii. 146 and xx. 90. (Akh, S.) ―         -b2-  Also, (S, A, K,) inf. ns. as above, (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man praying, A and TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"raised his voice in prayer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"supplication:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Th, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he cried out:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Es-Suddee, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he cried out, calling for aid,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"succour; humbled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abased, himself, and raised his voice:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he humbled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abased, himself, with earnest supplication;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AilaY A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"اِلَى ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"page_break","n":370},{"kind":"text","text":"to God; (S;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and cried out,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"called, for aid,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"succour."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) [Accord. to Katádeh,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yajoA^aruwna","text_ar":"يَجْاَرُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the Kur xxiii. 66 signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaxoraEuwna","text_ar":"يَخْرَعُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as written in the TA; but this is app. a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yajozaEuwna","text_ar":"يَجْزَعُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They manifest grief and agitation;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.] ―         -b3-  Also (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a plant)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"grew tall;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K;) like as one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAHati Al$~ajarapu","text_ar":"صَاحَتِ الشَّجَرَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA^arati AlA^aroDu","text_ar":"جَاَرَتِ الاَرْضُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The plants,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herbage, of the land grew tall."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","K","Th"]},{"entry_id":"n4882","headword_ar":"جَاْرٌ","root":"jA^r","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", applied to herbage, (Az, A, K,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fresh, juicy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sappy:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tall, and fullgrown:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abundant."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gayovN jaA^orN","text_ar":"غَيْثٌ جَاْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"juw^arN","text_ar":"جُوَرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (As, S, A, K,) and, accord. to As, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"juw^aArN","text_ar":"جُوَارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jawar~N","text_ar":"جَوَرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jiwar~N","text_ar":"جِوَرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A copious rain;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, S, A, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that makes the plants,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herbage, to grow tall:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) or the second,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a rain that makes a sound,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"noise."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Az","A","K","TA","As","S"]},{"entry_id":"n5407","headword_ar":"جَارٌّ","root":"jr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[act. part. n. of 1;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Dragging, drawing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAr~u AlD~abuEi","text_ar":"جَارُّ الضَّبُعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Rain that draws the hyena from its hole by its violence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the most violent rain;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though it left nothing without dragging it along: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rain that leaves nothing without making it to flow, and dragging it along:"},{"kind":"page_break","n":402},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the torrent that draws forth the hyena from its hole:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlD~abuEi","text_ar":"الضَّبُعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"majar~u","text_ar":"مَجَرُّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the torrent that has torn up the ground;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though the hyena were dragged along in it. (IAar, Sh, TA.) You say also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maTarN jaAr~u AlD~abuEi","text_ar":"مَطَرٌ جَارُّ الضَّبُعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maTorapN jaAr~apu AlD~abuEi","text_ar":"مَطْرَةٌ جَارَّةُ الضَّبُعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ibilN jaAr~apN","text_ar":"اـِبِلٌ جَارَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Working camels;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because they drag along burdens; (A, Mgh;) or tropically so called because they are dragged along by their nose-reins: (Mgh:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camels that are dragged along by their nosereins:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA: [but in the copies of the S, and in those of the K, in my possession,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tajur~u","text_ar":"تَجُرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tujar~u","text_ar":"تُجَرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", though the latter is evidently meant, as is shown by what here follows:])"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jAr~p","text_ar":"جارّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAEilapN","text_ar":"فَاعِلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafoEuwlapN","text_ar":"مَفْعُولَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": it is like as when you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eiy$apN raADayapN","text_ar":"عِيشَةٌ رَاضَيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maroDiy~apN","text_ar":"مَرْضِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA='N daAfiqN","text_ar":"مَا=ءٌ دَافِقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"madofuwqN","text_ar":"مَدْفُوقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) or it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as carry goods, or furniture and utensils, and wheat,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"food."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAn~N","text_ar":"حَانٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.) It is said in a trad. that there is no poor-rate ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sadaqap","text_ar":"صَدَقَة"},{"kind":"text","text":") in the case of such camels, (S, Mgh,) because they are the ridingcamels of the people; for the poor-rate is in the case of pasturing camels, exclusively of the working. (S.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA jaAr~a liY fiY h`*aA","text_ar":"لَا جَارَّ لِى فِى هٰذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is no profit for me in this to attract me to it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAr~N jaAr~N","text_ar":"حَارٌّ جَارٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an expression in which the latter word is an imitative sequent to the former; (S, K;) but accord. to A 'Obeyd, it was more common to say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAr~N yaAr~N","text_ar":"حَارٌّ يَارٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) and one says also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Har~aAnu yar~aAnu jar~aAnu","text_ar":"حَرَّانُ يَرَّانُ جَرَّانُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hr","text_ar":"حر"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["TA","IAar","A","Mgh","S"]},{"entry_id":"n5641","headword_ar":"جَارٍ","root":"jrY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"applied to water [and the like], ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Running,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flowing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pressing forward, in a downward"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a level course."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b2-  Also, [as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Running,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] applied to a horse and the like. (Msb.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadaqapN jaAriyapN","text_ar":"صَدَقَةٌ جَارِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A permanent, continuous, charitable donation; such as the unalienable legacies provided for various benevolent purposes."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n6665","headword_ar":"جَارَ","root":"jwr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yajuwru","text_ar":"يَجُورُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaworN","text_ar":"جَوْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He declined,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deviated, from the right course;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A;) and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jArEani AlqaSodi","text_ar":"جارعَنِ القَصْدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he wandered from the right way:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he pursued a wrong course:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he left the right way in journeying:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(anything)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"declined."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jAr Eani AlT~iriyqi","text_ar":"جار عَنِ الطِّرِيقِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He declined,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deviated, from the road,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"way."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jAr","text_ar":"جار"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb,) aor. as above, (Msb,) and so the inf. n., (Mgh, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He acted wrongfully, unjustly, injuriously,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tyrannically,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * Mgh, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayohi","text_ar":"عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"against him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY","text_ar":"فِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hukomihi","text_ar":"حُكْمِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in his judgment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY AlHukomi","text_ar":"فِى الحُكْمِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in judgment."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jArti AlA^aroDu","text_ar":"جارتِ الاَرْضُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The plants,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herbage, of the land grew tall:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA:) and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA^arat","text_ar":"جَاَرَت"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)       -A2-  See also 10."}],"source_refs":["TA","S","A","K","Mgh","Msb"]},{"entry_id":"n6672","headword_ar":"جَارٌ","root":"jwr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A neighbour; one who lives near to another;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one who lives in the next tent"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"house:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, Th, T, Msb:) pl. [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jiyraAnN","text_ar":"جِيرَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K) [and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jiwaArN","text_ar":"جِوَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a pl. not of unfrequent occurrence, and mentioned by Freytag as used by El-Mutanebbee,)] and [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jiyrapN","text_ar":"جِيرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajowaArN","text_ar":"اَجْوَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAEN","text_ar":"قَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qiyEaAnN","text_ar":"قِيعَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qiyEapN","text_ar":"قِيعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqowaAEN","text_ar":"اَقْوَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the only similar instance: (TA:) fem. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mgh.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AljaAru *uw AlqurobaY","text_ar":"الجَارُ ذُو القُرْبَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the Kur iv. 40] is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The relation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kinsman, who is abiding in one's neighbourhood:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who is abiding in one town or district or the like while thou art in another, and who has that title to respect which belongs to nearness of relationship:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the near neighbour:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd, Jel:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the near relation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jel:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he who is near, and connected, by relationship"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"religion."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAru Aljanobi","text_ar":"جَارُ الجَنْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AljaAru Aljunubu","text_ar":"الجَارُ الجُنُبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAru Aljunubi","text_ar":"جَارُ الجُنُبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jnb","text_ar":"جنب"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaArN nif~iyjN","text_ar":"جَارٌ نِفِّيجٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A stranger"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who has become one's neighbour"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A person whom one protects from wrongful, unjust, injurious,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tyrannical, treatment."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One who seeks,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"asks, protection"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K) of another:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAruka","text_ar":"جَارُكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he who seeks thy protection."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A protector;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Mgh, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one who protects another from that which he fears;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one who grants refuge,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"protects,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"preserves."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHeyth.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino *`lika AlA^amori","text_ar":"مِنْ ذٰلِكَ الاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humo jaArapN","text_ar":"هُمْ جَارَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They are protectors from that thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a phrase mentioned by Th, respecting which ISd says, I know not how this is, unless the sing. be supposed to be originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAy^irN","text_ar":"جَايِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", so as to have a pl. of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEalapN","text_ar":"فَعَلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaArapN","text_ar":"جَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jawarapN","text_ar":"جَوَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An aider,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"assister."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, Msb, K.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A confederate."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, Msb, K.) ―         -b7-  A woman's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"husband."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K.) ―         -b8-  A man's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wife;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaArapN","text_ar":"جَارَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, M, A, Mgh, Msb, K:) or the latter, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"object of"},{"kind":"text","text":"his"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"love:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) and the latter also, a woman's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fellow-wife;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb, TA;) so called because the term"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dar~apN","text_ar":"ضَرَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is disliked, (Mgh, Msb,) as being of evil omen. (Mgh.) ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A partner who has not divided with his partner:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so in the trad."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AljaAru A^aHaq~u biSaqabihi","text_ar":"الجَارُ اَحَقُّ بِصَقَبِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[explained in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sqb","text_ar":"صقب"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; as is shown by another trad. (Az, Msb.) ―         -b10-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A partner,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sharer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in immoveable property, such as land and houses,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in merchandise,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whether he divide the property with the other or not,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whether he be partner in the whole or only in part."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b11-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One who divides with another."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K.) ―         -b12-  (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"froj","text_ar":"فرْج"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pudendum"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a woman:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anus;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaArapN","text_ar":"جَارَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IAar, K, TA.) ―         -b13-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the sea-shore"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is near to the places where people have alighted and taken up their abode."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K.)"}],"source_refs":["IAar","Th","T","Msb","K","TA","Bd","Jel","S","M","A","Mgh"]}]}}